The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, April 11: The government will spend Rs 30 crore to improve infrastructure in three of the most popular tourist attractions in the state the beaches of Digha, Shankarpur and Mandarmoni, the Dooars and two gard- ens earmarked for tea tourism. 

 The Centre will provide Rs 20 crore. Roads and parks will be built with the money and the places beautified, tourism minister Manab Mukherjee said.

 Calcutta: More than 70 children, including a five-month-old boy, fell ill after being given Hepatitis B vaccines in South 24-Parganas Kulpi on Tuesday. An NGO had conducted the camp.




